caption.text:
I like how Hyper Light Drifter makes you put together the story through visuals and musical cues rather than through dialogue or text. That's a nice touch, and it works really well for games like this.⁠
⁠
Like these giant robots for example. What are they exactly? What was their connection to the precursor civilization of the Hyper Light Drifter universe? Do they have any connection to our purpose as drifters?⁠
⁠

PS5 eliminerà molti limiti al divertimento, dice il creatore di Tamarin - Per quanto la next-gen di casa Sony non sia ancora stata annunciata ufficialmente, il poco che si conosce di PS5 ha spesso spinto sviluppatori di piccole o grandi software house a commentare con gioia la presenza di un SSD. Il vantaggio, come ben sappiamo, sarà legato a caricamenti più rapidi: chi non ama attendere meno per iniziare a giocare?
Di certo Chameleon Games, creatore di Tamarin – platform action ispirato dai classici di Rare -, è un fan dell’SSD di PS5 e, in una recente intervista rilasciata ai microfoni di GamingBolt, ha spigato perché. Omar Sawi, capo dello studio, ha affermato: “È grandioso perché i tempi di caricamento sono una rottura. È difficile nasconderli, inoltre. Abbiamo dovuto pensare molto a come farlo nell’attuale generazione, poiché non volevamo schermate di caricamento. Per questo abbiamo dovuto ideare i livelli attorno a questa necessità, per esempio rendendo un tunnel leggermente più lungo del necessario o creando un livello intermedio cos - Continua a leggere su www.informaticagames.com http://tinyurl.com/y62vxpv6 #informaticagames #games #ps4 #playstation4 #gamers #xbox #instagamer #game #nintendo #playstation #xboxone #videogame #gaming #games #gamer #videogames

Hatsune Miku was my obsession for a few years. My first figure (Figma) was Hatsune Miku. I remember when I first started photography, I had a tiny white digital camera, and I was posing Hatsune near flowers. This photo of Hatsune Miku is one of the first semi-professional pictures I took of her. The photo itself is about four years old. I wanted to share this older photo in hopes of one day when I take another; it will be ten times better. 💙

Tetris 99

Je l'ai pris en boîte pour la collection.

Il contient les DLC Arène Local, Bataille Partagée, les mises à jour gratuites et un abonnement de 12 mois au online 👍

Les +
- Du Tetris simple et efficace
- Les différents modes de jeux
- Les défis journaliers et ceux pour débloquer les avatars
- Différents fonds d'écrans à débloquer
- L'ost sympa
- Le jeu online qui tient la route (heureusement)
- Les grands prix

Les -
- Impossible de récupérer les fonds d'écrans des grands prix si on a pas participé
- La musique du menu
- Pas de mode explication ou entraînement
- Forcément répétitif

Ce Tetris 99 reste une valeur sûre, avec ses différents modes de jeux que ce soit en online ou local. Dommage que l'on soit obligé d'aller voir sur internet pour comprendre les différents mode d'attaque ou comment faire un T-Spin. Un bon jeu 😉

caption.text:
Rocky x Apollo, Batman x Superman, Pepito x Mario... ultimate team up for the @overwatchleague finals with the @lagladiators. That's right, videogames have PROFESSIONAL LEAGUES!!!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Keeping things true to Los Angeles, its sounds, food and art, we took over #DTLA to offer an experience for fans of #Overwatch and videogames.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
A live mural by @david_siqueiros , grandson of the famous mexican painter David Siqueiros and artist behind the third jersey, music by @que.madre and @djchikibaby, we even got @ilovemicheladas to skip #smorgasburg just for this special event... con todo y el pinshi #MicheMobil!!!!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Tacos on deck straight from Mexicali and the baddest aguas frescas thanks to @agualucha.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Thanks for your trust, can't wait to bring more of this to Blizzard and the rest of the Overwatch league.
#ShieldsUp
#VamosGladiators

caption.text:
Tate anyone? Oldie but Goodie updated for the new #shmupsareshooters hashtag 😁😁😁😁😁😁😁😁😁
A few people thought my post yesterday was a Batsugun poster in the background but it’s actually my TV with the game running in Tate mode. So I thought this would be a fun one to repost. .

The almighty Dobkeratops is resting after a rad week of Shootermania... and so am I. 😂🤣. All that’s left now is for all us to not forget this 🤘 tag and continue to use it for future shooter posts. Thanks again to all the awesome folks that made the week such an event. I merely facilitated... this tag belongs to all of us and the IG gaming community now. Whatever it becomes will be what we make of it. And a final shout out to @backlog_chan for coming up with the tag that became a movement 😂💪. I even learned that anime girls will mock you for playing on easy mode 🤣😂👍🏻
.
.

WHO KNEW THERE WAS A ACTUAL XBOX CAR ?
➡️The Fiat Limited Edition Xbox 💚
➡️Test Driver 2005 Fiat Promotional Invite. No physical disc, just a personalised Invite Letter and paper looking disc.
➡️👉PLEASE SWIPE LEFT TO SEE THE CAR & LETTER etc.——————————————————————⁣⁣⁣
—The £8995 OTR, Punto Xbox is based on the Punto Active Sport 1.2 16v, yet features a lower purchase price, while becoming available with almost £600 worth of exclusive features. These include black metallic paint, Xbox badging and interior mats, an MP3 player and 100W subwoofer, and steering wheel mounted audio controls. All of which adds to Punto Active Sport's attractive standard equipment package of 15 inch alloy wheels, sports bumpers and rear spoiler, 6-speaker radio/CD player, and leather steering wheel and gear lever knob.
The Stilo Xbox is priced at £11,995 OTR, some £500 more than the Stilo Active Sport 1.6 16v on which it is based, but with almost £1500 worth of added features, customers will benefit from almost £1000 of added value. Features include Xbox badging and interior mats, 17" alloy wheels, black metallic paint, MP3 player and 100W subwoofer, air conditioning, steering wheel mounted audio controls, and sports pedals.

Hi! 
My new godsend.
Robotron 1715M.
Office Machine from German Democratic Republic produced in 1984-1989 . Exported to all countries of  Soviet East Europe and USSR. Version for USSR.  Based on Zilog Z80 clone (U880 4mhz) made in GDR. No HDD. 2 x 5.25 FDD. 64k of RAM (up to 256k).
Operating system was SCP (CP/M clone) or UDOS (Z80-RIO clone). It was built for office work and had minimal graphics and sound capabilities.
Now I'm looking for keyboard!

caption.text:
So here is the first half of the photos that I took from my trip to the incredible @arcadeclubuk !!
As you can see there was absolutely tons to play on!
I went for the all access pass and had a wicked afternoon playing on some of my favourite games.
And it was so cool to see so many new arcade machines that I never even knew existed!
Unlike expo’s that I have been to, I pretty much had full reign on whatever I wanted to go on, there was so much to choose from that even if I couldn’t get on something for a few minutes, there were another 10 games that I wanted to play that were free to jump on 🤓
I also picked up a mug, sticker and t-shirt from their shop which I’ll add to the 2nd half of the photos that I’ll put up later!
I highly recommend everybody visits Arcade Club, they also have one in Leeds too which I’m going to drive up and visit in the next few weeks.
And they do food, beer, hot and cold drinks to help you with all the energy you need for a quality day of gaming!
Will post the rest of the photos in a few hours 🤓✌🏼
Thank you Arcade Club!
.

caption.text:
Haze (2008)
#freeradicaldesign #ubisoft

One of the earlier PS3 games that was given a large marketing push was Haze. So much so that Korn was involved in writing a song for it and saying publicly that "gaming for me is a religion and Haze is the shit!" This quote was joked about at the time by the GameSpot crew. It's honestly more memorable than the game itself.

Speaking of the game, Haze is mediocre at best with decent shooting action with a very typical story. It's the main character eventually defecting from the evil corporation to join the rebels in righting the wrongs.

The full Korn quote along with other photos of graphical glitches are included in my story section.

caption.text:
Ori and the blind forest:
Septiembre ha sido un mes de muchos lanzamientos excelentes pero no debes dejar pasar este increíble video juego cortesia de Microsoft,con un nivel artístico pocas veces visto que me recuerda un poco al diseño de los últimos Rayman, pero mejorado x10. El ritmo de juego es rápido, innovador, los movimientos de Ori son fluidos , veloces , llenos de acción desde el ataque, equivar , hasta algo tan sencillo como saltar y trepar. Cuando mueres puedes volver rápidamente al lugar donde tuviste dificultades y en ningún momento se vuelve tedioso repetir algunas situaciones, a diferencia de algunos juegos que el movimiento lento del personaje puede llegar a hartar si te ves en una situación que necesite mayor tiempo.
La música es genial , se acopla perfectamente a la ambientación de los escenarios, el tema principal es de lo más melancólico que he escuchado para un video juego y puede sonar en tu cabeza días.
Un metroidvania que para mi, pese a ser un juego del año 2016, permanece totalmente fresco y dio más impulso( junto a otros títulos ) a este género que tiene casi 30 años.
Muy recomendado.

Gameplay luchando si no mal recuerdo con el primer mini boss.

The Contra Anniversary Collection is the third of Konami’s releases in celebration of the company’s 50th birthday. Prior to the release of this collection they also put out an Arcade Classics Collection and the Castlevania Collection. This package has been developed in conjunction with M2, so you know from the get-go that this is going to be a perfectly polished collection which respects the originals!⠀
⠀
The game was then announced as a shadow drop during the 2019 E3 Nintendo Direct presentation. A brilliant moment for Contra fans where Konami announced the collection would be released following the presentation and also announced a new game in the series, Contra Rogue Corps, to be released in September.⠀
.⠀⠀⠀
